48void SpeculativeJIT::boxInt52(GPRReg sourceGPR, GPRReg targetGPR, DataFormat format)
49{
50 GPRReg tempGPR;
51 if (sourceGPR == targetGPR)
52 tempGPR = allocate();
53 else
54 tempGPR = targetGPR;
55
56 FPRReg fpr = fprAllocate();
57
58 if (format == DataFormatInt52)
59 m_jit.rshift64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::int52ShiftAmount), sourceGPR);
60 else
61 ASSERT(format == DataFormatStrictInt52);
62
63 m_jit.boxInt52(sourceGPR, targetGPR, tempGPR, fpr);
64
65 if (format == DataFormatInt52 && sourceGPR != targetGPR)
66 m_jit.lshift64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::int52ShiftAmount), sourceGPR);
67
68 if (tempGPR != targetGPR)
69 unlock(tempGPR);
70
71 unlock(fpr);
72}
73
74GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillJSValue(Edge edge)
75{
76 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = edge->virtualRegister();
77 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
78
79 switch (info.registerFormat()) {
80 case DataFormatNone: {
81 GPRReg gpr = allocate();
82
83 if (edge->hasConstant()) {
84 JSValue jsValue = edge->asJSValue();
85 m_jit.move(MacroAssembler::TrustedImm64(JSValue::encode(jsValue)), gpr);
86 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJS);
87 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderConstant);
88 } else {
89 DataFormat spillFormat = info.spillFormat();
90 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderSpilled);
91 switch (spillFormat) {
92 case DataFormatInt32: {
93 m_jit.load32(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
94 m_jit.or64(GPRInfo::numberTagRegister, gpr);
95 spillFormat = DataFormatJSInt32;
96 break;
97 }
98
99 default:
100 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
101 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, spillFormat & DataFormatJS, spillFormat);
102 break;
103 }
104 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, spillFormat);
105 }
106 return gpr;
107 }
108
109 case DataFormatInt32: {
110 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
111 // If the register has already been locked we need to take a copy.
112 // If not, we'll zero extend in place, so mark on the info that this is now type DataFormatInt32, not DataFormatJSInt32.
113 if (m_gprs.isLocked(gpr)) {
114 GPRReg result = allocate();
115 m_jit.or64(GPRInfo::numberTagRegister, gpr, result);
116 return result;
117 }
118 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
119 m_jit.or64(GPRInfo::numberTagRegister, gpr);
120 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSInt32);
121 return gpr;
122 }
123
124 case DataFormatCell:
125 // No retag required on JSVALUE64!
126 case DataFormatJS:
127 case DataFormatJSInt32:
128 case DataFormatJSDouble:
129 case DataFormatJSCell:
130 case DataFormatJSBoolean:
131 case DataFormatJSBigInt32: {
132 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
133 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
134 return gpr;
135 }
136
137 case DataFormatBoolean:
138 case DataFormatStorage:
139 case DataFormatDouble:
140 case DataFormatInt52:
141 // this type currently never occurs
142 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Bad data format");
143
144 default:
145 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Corrupt data format");
146 return InvalidGPRReg;
147 }
148}

150void SpeculativeJIT::cachedGetById(CodeOrigin origin, JSValueRegs base, JSValueRegs result, GPRReg stubInfoGPR, CacheableIdentifier identifier, JITCompiler::Jump slowPathTarget , SpillRegistersMode mode, AccessType type)
151{
152 cachedGetById(origin, base.gpr(), result.gpr(), stubInfoGPR, identifier, slowPathTarget, mode, type);
153}
154
155void SpeculativeJIT::cachedGetById(CodeOrigin codeOrigin, GPRReg baseGPR, GPRReg resultGPR, GPRReg stubInfoGPR, CacheableIdentifier identifier, JITCompiler::Jump slowPathTarget, SpillRegistersMode spillMode, AccessType type)
156{
157 CallSiteIndex callSite = m_jit.recordCallSiteAndGenerateExceptionHandlingOSRExitIfNeeded(codeOrigin, m_stream->size());
158 RegisterSet usedRegisters = this->usedRegisters();
159 if (spillMode == DontSpill) {
160 // We've already flushed registers to the stack, we don't need to spill these.
161 usedRegisters.set(baseGPR, false);
162 usedRegisters.set(resultGPR, false);
163 if (stubInfoGPR != InvalidGPRReg)
164 usedRegisters.set(stubInfoGPR, false);
165 }
166 JITGetByIdGenerator gen(
167 m_jit.codeBlock(), JITType::DFGJIT, codeOrigin, callSite, usedRegisters, identifier,
168 JSValueRegs(baseGPR), JSValueRegs(resultGPR), stubInfoGPR, type);
169 gen.generateFastPath(m_jit);
170
171 JITCompiler::JumpList slowCases;
172 slowCases.append(slowPathTarget);
173 slowCases.append(gen.slowPathJump());
174
175 std::unique_ptr<SlowPathGenerator> slowPath;
176 if (JITCode::useDataIC(JITType::DFGJIT)) {
177 slowPath = slowPathICCall(
178 slowCases, this, gen.stubInfo(), stubInfoGPR, CCallHelpers::Address(stubInfoGPR, StructureStubInfo::offsetOfSlowOperation()), appropriateOptimizingGetByIdFunction(type),
179 spillMode, ExceptionCheckRequirement::CheckNeeded,
180 resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(codeOrigin)), stubInfoGPR, baseGPR, identifier.rawBits());
181 } else {
182 slowPath = slowPathCall(
183 slowCases, this, appropriateOptimizingGetByIdFunction(type),
184 spillMode, ExceptionCheckRequirement::CheckNeeded,
185 resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(codeOrigin)), gen.stubInfo(), baseGPR, identifier.rawBits());
186 }
187
188 m_jit.addGetById(gen, slowPath.get());
189 addSlowPathGenerator(WTFMove(slowPath));
190}
191
192void SpeculativeJIT::cachedGetByIdWithThis(CodeOrigin codeOrigin, GPRReg baseGPR, GPRReg thisGPR, GPRReg resultGPR, GPRReg stubInfoGPR, CacheableIdentifier identifier, const JITCompiler::JumpList& slowPathTarget)
193{
194 CallSiteIndex callSite = m_jit.recordCallSiteAndGenerateExceptionHandlingOSRExitIfNeeded(codeOrigin, m_stream->size());
195 RegisterSet usedRegisters = this->usedRegisters();
196 // We've already flushed registers to the stack, we don't need to spill these.
197 usedRegisters.set(baseGPR, false);
198 usedRegisters.set(thisGPR, false);
199 usedRegisters.set(resultGPR, false);
200 if (stubInfoGPR != InvalidGPRReg)
201 usedRegisters.set(stubInfoGPR, false);
202
203 JITGetByIdWithThisGenerator gen(
204 m_jit.codeBlock(), JITType::DFGJIT, codeOrigin, callSite, usedRegisters, identifier,
205 JSValueRegs(resultGPR), JSValueRegs(baseGPR), JSValueRegs(thisGPR), stubInfoGPR);
206 gen.generateFastPath(m_jit);
207
208 JITCompiler::JumpList slowCases;
209 slowCases.append(slowPathTarget);
210 slowCases.append(gen.slowPathJump());
211
212 std::unique_ptr<SlowPathGenerator> slowPath;
213 if (JITCode::useDataIC(JITType::DFGJIT)) {
214 slowPath = slowPathICCall(
215 slowCases, this, gen.stubInfo(), stubInfoGPR, CCallHelpers::Address(stubInfoGPR, StructureStubInfo::offsetOfSlowOperation()), operationGetByIdWithThisOptimize,
216 DontSpill, ExceptionCheckRequirement::CheckNeeded,
217 resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(codeOrigin)), stubInfoGPR, baseGPR, thisGPR, identifier.rawBits());
218 } else {
219 slowPath = slowPathCall(
220 slowCases, this, operationGetByIdWithThisOptimize,
221 DontSpill, ExceptionCheckRequirement::CheckNeeded,
222 resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(codeOrigin)), gen.stubInfo(), baseGPR, thisGPR, identifier.rawBits());
223 }
224
225 m_jit.addGetByIdWithThis(gen, slowPath.get());
226 addSlowPathGenerator(WTFMove(slowPath));
227}

229void SpeculativeJIT::nonSpeculativeNonPeepholeCompareNullOrUndefined(Edge operand)
230{
231 JSValueOperand arg(this, operand, ManualOperandSpeculation);
232 GPRReg argGPR = arg.gpr();
233
234 GPRTemporary result(this);
235 GPRReg resultGPR = result.gpr();
236
237 m_jit.move(TrustedImm32(0), resultGPR);
238
239 JITCompiler::JumpList done;
240 if (masqueradesAsUndefinedWatchpointIsStillValid()) {
241 if (!isKnownNotCell(operand.node()))
242 done.append(m_jit.branchIfCell(JSValueRegs(argGPR)));
243 } else {
244 GPRTemporary localGlobalObject(this);
245 GPRTemporary remoteGlobalObject(this);
246 GPRTemporary scratch(this);
247
248 JITCompiler::Jump notCell;
249 if (!isKnownCell(operand.node()))
250 notCell = m_jit.branchIfNotCell(JSValueRegs(argGPR));
251
252 JITCompiler::Jump isNotMasqueradesAsUndefined = m_jit.branchTest8(
253 JITCompiler::Zero,
254 JITCompiler::Address(argGPR, JSCell::typeInfoFlagsOffset()),
255 JITCompiler::TrustedImm32(MasqueradesAsUndefined));
256 done.append(isNotMasqueradesAsUndefined);
257
258 GPRReg localGlobalObjectGPR = localGlobalObject.gpr();
259 GPRReg remoteGlobalObjectGPR = remoteGlobalObject.gpr();
260 m_jit.move(TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_jit.graph(), m_jit.graph().globalObjectFor(m_currentNode->origin.semantic)), localGlobalObjectGPR);
261 m_jit.emitLoadStructure(vm(), argGPR, resultGPR, scratch.gpr());
262 m_jit.loadPtr(JITCompiler::Address(resultGPR, Structure::globalObjectOffset()), remoteGlobalObjectGPR);
263 m_jit.comparePtr(JITCompiler::Equal, localGlobalObjectGPR, remoteGlobalObjectGPR, resultGPR);
264 done.append(m_jit.jump());
265 if (!isKnownCell(operand.node()))
266 notCell.link(&m_jit);
267 }
268
269 if (!isKnownNotOther(operand.node())) {
270 m_jit.move(argGPR, resultGPR);
271 m_jit.and64(JITCompiler::TrustedImm32(~JSValue::UndefinedTag), resultGPR);
272 m_jit.compare64(JITCompiler::Equal, resultGPR, JITCompiler::TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueNull), resultGPR);
273 }
274
275 done.link(&m_jit);
276
277 m_jit.or32(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), resultGPR);
278 jsValueResult(resultGPR, m_currentNode, DataFormatJSBoolean);
279}
280
281void SpeculativeJIT::nonSpeculativePeepholeBranchNullOrUndefined(Edge operand, Node* branchNode)
282{
283 BasicBlock* taken = branchNode->branchData()->taken.block;
284 BasicBlock* notTaken = branchNode->branchData()->notTaken.block;
285
286 JSValueOperand arg(this, operand, ManualOperandSpeculation);
287 GPRReg argGPR = arg.gpr();
288
289 GPRTemporary result(this, Reuse, arg);
290 GPRReg resultGPR = result.gpr();
291
292 // First, handle the case where "operand" is a cell.
293 if (masqueradesAsUndefinedWatchpointIsStillValid()) {
294 if (!isKnownNotCell(operand.node())) {
295 JITCompiler::Jump isCell = m_jit.branchIfCell(JSValueRegs(argGPR));
296 addBranch(isCell, notTaken);
297 }
298 } else {
299 GPRTemporary localGlobalObject(this);
300 GPRTemporary remoteGlobalObject(this);
301 GPRTemporary scratch(this);
302
303 JITCompiler::Jump notCell;
304 if (!isKnownCell(operand.node()))
305 notCell = m_jit.branchIfNotCell(JSValueRegs(argGPR));
306
307 branchTest8(JITCompiler::Zero,
308 JITCompiler::Address(argGPR, JSCell::typeInfoFlagsOffset()),
309 JITCompiler::TrustedImm32(MasqueradesAsUndefined), notTaken);
310
311 GPRReg localGlobalObjectGPR = localGlobalObject.gpr();
312 GPRReg remoteGlobalObjectGPR = remoteGlobalObject.gpr();
313 m_jit.move(TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_jit.graph(), m_jit.graph().globalObjectFor(m_currentNode->origin.semantic)), localGlobalObjectGPR);
314 m_jit.emitLoadStructure(vm(), argGPR, resultGPR, scratch.gpr());
315 m_jit.loadPtr(JITCompiler::Address(resultGPR, Structure::globalObjectOffset()), remoteGlobalObjectGPR);
316 branchPtr(JITCompiler::Equal, localGlobalObjectGPR, remoteGlobalObjectGPR, taken);
317
318 if (!isKnownCell(operand.node())) {
319 jump(notTaken, ForceJump);
320 notCell.link(&m_jit);
321 }
322 }
323
324 if (isKnownNotOther(operand.node()))
325 jump(notTaken);
326 else {
327 JITCompiler::RelationalCondition condition = JITCompiler::Equal;
328 if (taken == nextBlock()) {
329 condition = JITCompiler::NotEqual;
330 std::swap(taken, notTaken);
331 }
332 m_jit.move(argGPR, resultGPR);
333 m_jit.and64(JITCompiler::TrustedImm32(~JSValue::UndefinedTag), resultGPR);
334 branch64(condition, resultGPR, JITCompiler::TrustedImm64(JSValue::ValueNull), taken);
335 jump(notTaken);
336 }
337}
338
339void SpeculativeJIT::nonSpeculativePeepholeStrictEq(Node* node, Node* branchNode, bool invert)
340{
341 BasicBlock* taken = branchNode->branchData()->taken.block;
342 BasicBlock* notTaken = branchNode->branchData()->notTaken.block;
343
344 // The branch instruction will branch to the taken block.
345 // If taken is next, switch taken with notTaken & invert the branch condition so we can fall through.
346 if (taken == nextBlock()) {
347 invert = !invert;
348 BasicBlock* tmp = taken;
349 taken = notTaken;
350 notTaken = tmp;
351 }
352
353 ASSERT(node->isBinaryUseKind(UntypedUse) || node->isBinaryUseKind(AnyBigIntUse));
354 JSValueOperand arg1(this, node->child1(), ManualOperandSpeculation);
355 JSValueOperand arg2(this, node->child2(), ManualOperandSpeculation);
356 speculate(node, node->child1());
357 speculate(node, node->child2());
358 GPRReg arg1GPR = arg1.gpr();
359 GPRReg arg2GPR = arg2.gpr();
360
361 GPRTemporary result(this);
362 GPRReg resultGPR = result.gpr();
363
364 arg1.use();
365 arg2.use();
366
367 if (isKnownCell(node->child1().node()) && isKnownCell(node->child2().node())) {
368 // see if we get lucky: if the arguments are cells and they reference the same
369 // cell, then they must be strictly equal.
370 branch64(JITCompiler::Equal, arg1GPR, arg2GPR, invert ? notTaken : taken);
371
372 silentSpillAllRegisters(resultGPR);
373 callOperation(operationCompareStrictEqCell, resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)), arg1GPR, arg2GPR);
374 silentFillAllRegisters();
375 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
376
377 branchTest32(invert ? JITCompiler::Zero : JITCompiler::NonZero, resultGPR, taken);
378 } else {
379 /* At a high level we do (assuming 'invert' to be false):
380 If (left is Double || right is Double)
381 goto slowPath;
382 if (left == right)
383 goto taken;
384 if (left is Cell || right is Cell)
385 goto slowPath;
386 goto notTaken;
387 */
388
389 JITCompiler::JumpList slowPathCases;
390
391 // This fragment implements (left is Double || right is Double), with a single branch instead of the 4 that would be naively required if we used branchIfInt32/branchIfNumber
392 // The trick is that if a JSValue is an Int32, then adding 1<<49 to it will make it overflow, leaving all high bits at 0
393 // If it is not a number at all, then 1<<49 will be its only high bit set
394 // Leaving only doubles above or equal 1<<50.
395 GPRTemporary scratch(this);
396 m_jit.move(arg1GPR, resultGPR);
397 m_jit.move(arg2GPR, scratch.gpr());
398 m_jit.add64(TrustedImm64(JSValue::LowestOfHighBits), resultGPR);
399 m_jit.add64(TrustedImm64(JSValue::LowestOfHighBits), scratch.gpr());
400 m_jit.or64(scratch.gpr(), resultGPR, resultGPR);
401 constexpr uint64_t nextLowestOfHighBits = JSValue::LowestOfHighBits << 1;
402 slowPathCases.append(m_jit.branch64(JITCompiler::AboveOrEqual, resultGPR, TrustedImm64(nextLowestOfHighBits)));
403
404 branch64(JITCompiler::Equal, arg1GPR, arg2GPR, invert ? notTaken : taken);
405
406 // If we support BigInt32 we must go to a slow path if at least one operand is a cell (for HeapBigInt === BigInt32)
407 // If we don't support BigInt32, we only have to go to a slow path if both operands are cells (for HeapBigInt === HeapBigInt and String === String)
408 // Instead of doing two branches, we can do a single one, by observing that
409 // 1. (left is Cell && right is Cell) is the same as ((left | right) is Cell)
410 // Both are "All high bits are 0"
411 // 2. Since we know that neither is a double, (left is Cell || right is Cell) is equivalent to ((left & right) is Cell)
412 // If both are Int32, then the top bits will be set and the test will fail
413 // If at least one is not Int32, then the top bits will be 0.
414 // And if at least one is a cell, then the 'Other' tag will also be 0, making the test succeed
415#if USE(BIGINT32)
416 m_jit.and64(arg1GPR, arg2GPR, resultGPR);
417#else
418 m_jit.or64(arg1GPR, arg2GPR, resultGPR);
419#endif
420 slowPathCases.append(m_jit.branchIfCell(resultGPR));
421
422 jump(invert ? taken : notTaken, ForceJump);
423
424 addSlowPathGenerator(slowPathCall(slowPathCases, this, operationCompareStrictEq, resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)), arg1GPR, arg2GPR));
425 branchTest32(invert ? JITCompiler::Zero : JITCompiler::NonZero, resultGPR, taken);
426 }
427
428 jump(notTaken);
429}
430
431void SpeculativeJIT::genericJSValueNonPeepholeStrictEq(Node* node, bool invert)
432{
433 // FIXME: some of this code should be shareable with nonSpeculativePeepholeStrictEq
434 JSValueOperand arg1(this, node->child1(), ManualOperandSpeculation);
435 JSValueOperand arg2(this, node->child2(), ManualOperandSpeculation);
436 speculate(node, node->child1());
437 speculate(node, node->child2());
438 JSValueRegs arg1Regs = arg1.jsValueRegs();
439 JSValueRegs arg2Regs = arg2.jsValueRegs();
440 GPRReg arg1GPR = arg1.gpr();
441 GPRReg arg2GPR = arg2.gpr();
442
443 GPRTemporary result(this);
444 GPRReg resultGPR = result.gpr();
445
446 arg1.use();
447 arg2.use();
448
449 if (isKnownCell(node->child1().node()) && isKnownCell(node->child2().node())) {
450 // see if we get lucky: if the arguments are cells and they reference the same
451 // cell, then they must be strictly equal.
452 // FIXME: this should flush registers instead of silent spill/fill.
453 JITCompiler::Jump notEqualCase = m_jit.branch64(JITCompiler::NotEqual, arg1Regs.gpr(), arg2Regs.gpr());
454
455 m_jit.move(JITCompiler::TrustedImm64(!invert), resultGPR);
456
457 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.jump();
458
459 notEqualCase.link(&m_jit);
460
461 silentSpillAllRegisters(resultGPR);
462 callOperation(operationCompareStrictEqCell, resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)), arg1Regs, arg2Regs);
463 silentFillAllRegisters();
464 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
465
466 done.link(&m_jit);
467 unblessedBooleanResult(resultGPR, m_currentNode, UseChildrenCalledExplicitly);
468 return;
469 }
470 /* At a high level we do (assuming 'invert' to be false):
471 If (left is Double || right is Double)
472 goto slowPath;
473 result = (left == right);
474 if (result)
475 goto done;
476 if (left is Cell || right is Cell)
477 goto slowPath;
478 done:
479 return result;
480 */
481
482 JITCompiler::JumpList slowPathCases;
483
484 // This fragment implements (left is Double || right is Double), with a single branch instead of the 4 that would be naively required if we used branchIfInt32/branchIfNumber
485 // The trick is that if a JSValue is an Int32, then adding 1<<49 to it will make it overflow, leaving all high bits at 0
486 // If it is not a number at all, then 1<<49 will be its only high bit set
487 // Leaving only doubles above or equal 1<<50.
488 GPRTemporary scratch(this);
489 m_jit.move(arg1GPR, resultGPR);
490 m_jit.move(arg2GPR, scratch.gpr());
491 m_jit.add64(TrustedImm64(JSValue::LowestOfHighBits), resultGPR);
492 m_jit.add64(TrustedImm64(JSValue::LowestOfHighBits), scratch.gpr());
493 m_jit.or64(scratch.gpr(), resultGPR, resultGPR);
494 constexpr uint64_t nextLowestOfHighBits = JSValue::LowestOfHighBits << 1;
495 slowPathCases.append(m_jit.branch64(JITCompiler::AboveOrEqual, resultGPR, TrustedImm64(nextLowestOfHighBits)));
496
497 m_jit.compare64(JITCompiler::Equal, arg1GPR, arg2GPR, resultGPR);
498 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.branchTest64(JITCompiler::NonZero, resultGPR);
499
500 // If we support BigInt32 we must go to a slow path if at least one operand is a cell (for HeapBigInt === BigInt32)
501 // If we don't support BigInt32, we only have to go to a slow path if both operands are cells (for HeapBigInt === HeapBigInt and String === String)
502 // Instead of doing two branches, we can do a single one, by observing that
503 // 1. (left is Cell && right is Cell) is the same as ((left | right) is Cell)
504 // Both are "All high bits are 0"
505 // 2. Since we know that neither is a double, (left is Cell || right is Cell) is equivalent to ((left & right) is Cell)
506 // If both are Int32, then the top bits will be set and the test will fail
507 // If at least one is not Int32, then the top bits will be 0.
508 // And if at least one is a cell, then the 'Other' tag will also be 0, making the test succeed
509#if USE(BIGINT32)
510 m_jit.and64(arg1GPR, arg2GPR, resultGPR);
511#else
512 m_jit.or64(arg1GPR, arg2GPR, resultGPR);
513#endif
514 slowPathCases.append(m_jit.branchIfCell(resultGPR));
515
516 m_jit.move(TrustedImm64(0), resultGPR);
517
518 addSlowPathGenerator(slowPathCall(slowPathCases, this, operationCompareStrictEq, resultGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)), arg1Regs, arg2Regs));
519
520 done.link(&m_jit);
521
522 m_jit.xor64(TrustedImm64(invert), resultGPR);
523
524 unblessedBooleanResult(resultGPR, m_currentNode, UseChildrenCalledExplicitly);
525}
526
527void SpeculativeJIT::emitCall(Node* node)
528{
529 CallLinkInfo::CallType callType;
530 bool isVarargs = false;
531 bool isForwardVarargs = false;
532 bool isTail = false;
533 bool isEmulatedTail = false;
534 bool isDirect = false;
535 switch (node->op()) {
536 case Call:
537 case CallEval:
538 callType = CallLinkInfo::Call;
539 break;
540 case TailCall:
541 callType = CallLinkInfo::TailCall;
542 isTail = true;
543 break;
544 case TailCallInlinedCaller:
545 callType = CallLinkInfo::Call;
546 isEmulatedTail = true;
547 break;
548 case Construct:
549 callType = CallLinkInfo::Construct;
550 break;
551 case CallVarargs:
552 callType = CallLinkInfo::CallVarargs;
553 isVarargs = true;
554 break;
555 case TailCallVarargs:
556 callType = CallLinkInfo::TailCallVarargs;
557 isVarargs = true;
558 isTail = true;
559 break;
560 case TailCallVarargsInlinedCaller:
561 callType = CallLinkInfo::CallVarargs;
562 isVarargs = true;
563 isEmulatedTail = true;
564 break;
565 case ConstructVarargs:
566 callType = CallLinkInfo::ConstructVarargs;
567 isVarargs = true;
568 break;
569 case CallForwardVarargs:
570 callType = CallLinkInfo::CallVarargs;
571 isForwardVarargs = true;
572 break;
573 case ConstructForwardVarargs:
574 callType = CallLinkInfo::ConstructVarargs;
575 isForwardVarargs = true;
576 break;
577 case TailCallForwardVarargs:
578 callType = CallLinkInfo::TailCallVarargs;
579 isTail = true;
580 isForwardVarargs = true;
581 break;
582 case TailCallForwardVarargsInlinedCaller:
583 callType = CallLinkInfo::CallVarargs;
584 isEmulatedTail = true;
585 isForwardVarargs = true;
586 break;
587 case DirectCall:
588 callType = CallLinkInfo::DirectCall;
589 isDirect = true;
590 break;
591 case DirectConstruct:
592 callType = CallLinkInfo::DirectConstruct;
593 isDirect = true;
594 break;
595 case DirectTailCall:
596 callType = CallLinkInfo::DirectTailCall;
597 isTail = true;
598 isDirect = true;
599 break;
600 case DirectTailCallInlinedCaller:
601 callType = CallLinkInfo::DirectCall;
602 isEmulatedTail = true;
603 isDirect = true;
604 break;
605 default:
606 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), node, "bad node type");
607 break;
608 }
609
610 GPRReg calleeGPR = InvalidGPRReg;
611 CallFrameShuffleData shuffleData;
612
613 JSGlobalObject* globalObject = m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic);
614 ExecutableBase* executable = nullptr;
615 FunctionExecutable* functionExecutable = nullptr;
616 if (isDirect) {
617 executable = node->castOperand<ExecutableBase*>();
618 functionExecutable = jsDynamicCast<FunctionExecutable*>(vm(), executable);
619 }
620
621 unsigned numPassedArgs = 0;
622 unsigned numAllocatedArgs = 0;
623
624 // Gotta load the arguments somehow. Varargs is trickier.
625 if (isVarargs || isForwardVarargs) {
626 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isDirect);
627 CallVarargsData* data = node->callVarargsData();
628
629 int numUsedStackSlots = m_jit.graph().m_nextMachineLocal;
630
631 if (isForwardVarargs) {
632 flushRegisters();
633 if (node->child3())
634 use(node->child3());
635
636 GPRReg scratchGPR1;
637 GPRReg scratchGPR2;
638 GPRReg scratchGPR3;
639
640 scratchGPR1 = JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR();
641 scratchGPR2 = JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR(scratchGPR1);
642 scratchGPR3 = JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR(scratchGPR1, scratchGPR2);
643
644 m_jit.move(TrustedImm32(numUsedStackSlots), scratchGPR2);
645 JITCompiler::JumpList slowCase;
646 InlineCallFrame* inlineCallFrame;
647 if (node->child3())
648 inlineCallFrame = node->child3()->origin.semantic.inlineCallFrame();
649 else
650 inlineCallFrame = node->origin.semantic.inlineCallFrame();
651 // emitSetupVarargsFrameFastCase modifies the stack pointer if it succeeds.
652 emitSetupVarargsFrameFastCase(vm(), m_jit, scratchGPR2, scratchGPR1, scratchGPR2, scratchGPR3, inlineCallFrame, data->firstVarArgOffset, slowCase);
653 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.jump();
654 slowCase.link(&m_jit);
655 callOperation(operationThrowStackOverflowForVarargs, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, globalObject));
656 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
657 m_jit.abortWithReason(DFGVarargsThrowingPathDidNotThrow);
658 done.link(&m_jit);
659 } else {
660 GPRReg argumentsGPR;
661 GPRReg scratchGPR1;
662 GPRReg scratchGPR2;
663 GPRReg scratchGPR3;
664
665 auto loadArgumentsGPR = [&] (GPRReg reservedGPR) {
666 if (reservedGPR != InvalidGPRReg)
667 lock(reservedGPR);
668 JSValueOperand arguments(this, node->child3());
669 argumentsGPR = arguments.gpr();
670 if (reservedGPR != InvalidGPRReg)
671 unlock(reservedGPR);
672 flushRegisters();
673
674 scratchGPR1 = JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR(argumentsGPR, reservedGPR);
675 scratchGPR2 = JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR(argumentsGPR, scratchGPR1, reservedGPR);
676 scratchGPR3 = JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR(argumentsGPR, scratchGPR1, scratchGPR2, reservedGPR);
677 };
678
679 loadArgumentsGPR(InvalidGPRReg);
680
681 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), node, isFlushed());
682
683 // Right now, arguments is in argumentsGPR and the register file is flushed.
684 callOperation(operationSizeFrameForVarargs, GPRInfo::returnValueGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)), argumentsGPR, numUsedStackSlots, data->firstVarArgOffset);
685 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
686
687 // Now we have the argument count of the callee frame, but we've lost the arguments operand.
688 // Reconstruct the arguments operand while preserving the callee frame.
689 loadArgumentsGPR(GPRInfo::returnValueGPR);
690 m_jit.move(TrustedImm32(numUsedStackSlots), scratchGPR1);
691 emitSetVarargsFrame(m_jit, GPRInfo::returnValueGPR, false, scratchGPR1, scratchGPR1);
692 m_jit.addPtr(TrustedImm32(-(sizeof(CallerFrameAndPC) + WTF::roundUpToMultipleOf(stackAlignmentBytes(), 5 * sizeof(void*)))), scratchGPR1, JITCompiler::stackPointerRegister);
693
694 callOperation(operationSetupVarargsFrame, GPRInfo::returnValueGPR, TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)), scratchGPR1, argumentsGPR, data->firstVarArgOffset, GPRInfo::returnValueGPR);
695 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
696 m_jit.addPtr(TrustedImm32(sizeof(CallerFrameAndPC)), GPRInfo::returnValueGPR, JITCompiler::stackPointerRegister);
697 }
698
699 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), node, isFlushed());
700
701 // We don't need the arguments array anymore.
702 if (isVarargs)
703 use(node->child3());
704
705 // Now set up the "this" argument.
706 JSValueOperand thisArgument(this, node->child2());
707 GPRReg thisArgumentGPR = thisArgument.gpr();
708 thisArgument.use();
709
710 m_jit.store64(thisArgumentGPR, JITCompiler::calleeArgumentSlot(0));
711 } else {
712 // The call instruction's first child is the function; the subsequent children are the
713 // arguments.
714 numPassedArgs = node->numChildren() - 1;
715 numAllocatedArgs = numPassedArgs;
716
717 if (functionExecutable) {
718 // Allocate more args if this would let us avoid arity checks. This is throttled by
719 // CallLinkInfo's limit. It's probably good to throttle it - if the callee wants a
720 // ginormous amount of argument space then it's better for them to do it so that when we
721 // make calls to other things, we don't waste space.
722 unsigned desiredNumAllocatedArgs = static_cast<unsigned>(functionExecutable->parameterCount()) + 1;
723 if (desiredNumAllocatedArgs <= Options::maximumDirectCallStackSize()) {
724 numAllocatedArgs = std::max(numAllocatedArgs, desiredNumAllocatedArgs);
725
726 // Whoever converts to DirectCall should do this adjustment. It's too late for us to
727 // do this adjustment now since we will have already emitted code that relied on the
728 // value of m_parameterSlots.
729 DFG_ASSERT(
730 m_jit.graph(), node,
731 Graph::parameterSlotsForArgCount(numAllocatedArgs)
732 <= m_jit.graph().m_parameterSlots);
733 }
734 }
735
736 if (isTail) {
737 Edge calleeEdge = m_jit.graph().child(node, 0);
738 JSValueOperand callee(this, calleeEdge);
739 calleeGPR = callee.gpr();
740 if (!isDirect)
741 callee.use();
742
743 shuffleData.numberTagRegister = GPRInfo::numberTagRegister;
744 shuffleData.numLocals = m_jit.graph().frameRegisterCount();
745 shuffleData.callee = ValueRecovery::inGPR(calleeGPR, DataFormatJS);
746 shuffleData.args.resize(numAllocatedArgs);
747 shuffleData.numPassedArgs = numPassedArgs;
748
749 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numPassedArgs; ++i) {
750 Edge argEdge = m_jit.graph().varArgChild(node, i + 1);
751 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfo(argEdge.node());
752 if (!isDirect)
753 use(argEdge);
754 shuffleData.args[i] = info.recovery(argEdge->virtualRegister());
755 }
756
757 for (unsigned i = numPassedArgs; i < numAllocatedArgs; ++i)
758 shuffleData.args[i] = ValueRecovery::constant(jsUndefined());
759
760 shuffleData.setupCalleeSaveRegisters(m_jit.codeBlock());
761 } else {
762 m_jit.store32(MacroAssembler::TrustedImm32(numPassedArgs), JITCompiler::calleeFramePayloadSlot(CallFrameSlot::argumentCountIncludingThis));
763
764 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numPassedArgs; i++) {
765 Edge argEdge = m_jit.graph().m_varArgChildren[node->firstChild() + 1 + i];
766 JSValueOperand arg(this, argEdge);
767 GPRReg argGPR = arg.gpr();
768 use(argEdge);
769
770 m_jit.store64(argGPR, JITCompiler::calleeArgumentSlot(i));
771 }
772
773 for (unsigned i = numPassedArgs; i < numAllocatedArgs; ++i)
774 m_jit.storeTrustedValue(jsUndefined(), JITCompiler::calleeArgumentSlot(i));
775 }
776 }
777
778 if (!isTail || isVarargs || isForwardVarargs) {
779 Edge calleeEdge = m_jit.graph().child(node, 0);
780 JSValueOperand callee(this, calleeEdge);
781 calleeGPR = callee.gpr();
782 callee.use();
783 m_jit.store64(calleeGPR, JITCompiler::calleeFrameSlot(CallFrameSlot::callee));
784
785 flushRegisters();
786 }
787
788 CodeOrigin staticOrigin = node->origin.semantic;
789 InlineCallFrame* staticInlineCallFrame = staticOrigin.inlineCallFrame();
790 ASSERT(!isTail || !staticInlineCallFrame || !staticInlineCallFrame->getCallerSkippingTailCalls());
791 ASSERT(!isEmulatedTail || (staticInlineCallFrame && staticInlineCallFrame->getCallerSkippingTailCalls()));
792 CodeOrigin dynamicOrigin =
793 isEmulatedTail ? *staticInlineCallFrame->getCallerSkippingTailCalls() : staticOrigin;
794
795 CallSiteIndex callSite = m_jit.recordCallSiteAndGenerateExceptionHandlingOSRExitIfNeeded(dynamicOrigin, m_stream->size());
796
797 auto setResultAndResetStack = [&] () {
798 GPRFlushedCallResult result(this);
799 GPRReg resultGPR = result.gpr();
800 m_jit.move(GPRInfo::returnValueGPR, resultGPR);
801
802 jsValueResult(resultGPR, m_currentNode, DataFormatJS, UseChildrenCalledExplicitly);
803
804 // After the calls are done, we need to reestablish our stack
805 // pointer. We rely on this for varargs calls, calls with arity
806 // mismatch (the callframe is slided) and tail calls.
807 m_jit.addPtr(TrustedImm32(m_jit.graph().stackPointerOffset() * sizeof(Register)), GPRInfo::callFrameRegister, JITCompiler::stackPointerRegister);
808 };
809
810 CallLinkInfo* callLinkInfo = m_jit.codeBlock()->addCallLinkInfo(m_currentNode->origin.semantic);
811 callLinkInfo->setUpCall(callType, calleeGPR);
812
813 if (node->op() == CallEval) {
814 // We want to call operationCallEval but we don't want to overwrite the parameter area in
815 // which we have created a prototypical eval call frame. This means that we have to
816 // subtract stack to make room for the call. Lucky for us, at this point we have the whole
817 // register file to ourselves.
818
819 m_jit.emitStoreCallSiteIndex(callSite);
820 m_jit.addPtr(TrustedImm32(-static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(sizeof(CallerFrameAndPC))), JITCompiler::stackPointerRegister, GPRInfo::regT0);
821 m_jit.storePtr(GPRInfo::callFrameRegister, JITCompiler::Address(GPRInfo::regT0, CallFrame::callerFrameOffset()));
822
823 // Now we need to make room for:
824 // - The caller frame and PC of a call to operationCallEval.
825 // - Potentially two arguments on the stack.
826 unsigned requiredBytes = sizeof(CallerFrameAndPC) + sizeof(CallFrame*) * 2;
827 requiredBytes = WTF::roundUpToMultipleOf(stackAlignmentBytes(), requiredBytes);
828 m_jit.subPtr(TrustedImm32(requiredBytes), JITCompiler::stackPointerRegister);
829 m_jit.move(TrustedImm32(node->ecmaMode().value()), GPRInfo::regT1);
830 m_jit.setupArguments<decltype(operationCallEval)>(TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, globalObject), GPRInfo::regT0, GPRInfo::regT1);
831 prepareForExternalCall();
832 m_jit.appendCall(operationCallEval);
833 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
834 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.branchIfNotEmpty(GPRInfo::returnValueGPR);
835
836 // This is the part where we meant to make a normal call. Oops.
837 m_jit.addPtr(TrustedImm32(requiredBytes), JITCompiler::stackPointerRegister);
838 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::calleeFrameSlot(CallFrameSlot::callee), GPRInfo::regT0);
839 m_jit.emitVirtualCall(vm(), globalObject, callLinkInfo);
840
841 done.link(&m_jit);
842 setResultAndResetStack();
843 return;
844 }
845
846 if (isDirect) {
847 callLinkInfo->setExecutableDuringCompilation(executable);
848 callLinkInfo->setMaxArgumentCountIncludingThis(numAllocatedArgs);
849
850 if (isTail) {
851 RELEASE_ASSERT(node->op() == DirectTailCall);
852
853 JITCompiler::Label mainPath = m_jit.label();
854 m_jit.emitStoreCallSiteIndex(callSite);
855
856 callLinkInfo->emitDirectTailCallFastPath(m_jit, [&] {
857 callLinkInfo->setFrameShuffleData(shuffleData);
858 CallFrameShuffler(m_jit, shuffleData).prepareForTailCall();
859 });
860 JITCompiler::Label slowPath = m_jit.label();
861
862 silentSpillAllRegisters(InvalidGPRReg);
863 callOperation(operationLinkDirectCall, callLinkInfo, calleeGPR);
864 silentFillAllRegisters();
865 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
866 m_jit.jump().linkTo(mainPath, &m_jit);
867
868 useChildren(node);
869
870 m_jit.addJSDirectCall(slowPath, callLinkInfo);
871 return;
872 }
873
874 JITCompiler::Label mainPath = m_jit.label();
875 m_jit.emitStoreCallSiteIndex(callSite);
876 callLinkInfo->emitDirectFastPath(m_jit);
877 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.jump();
878
879 JITCompiler::Label slowPath = m_jit.label();
880 if (isX86())
881 m_jit.pop(JITCompiler::selectScratchGPR(calleeGPR));
882
883 callOperation(operationLinkDirectCall, callLinkInfo, calleeGPR);
884 m_jit.exceptionCheck();
885 m_jit.jump().linkTo(mainPath, &m_jit);
886
887 done.link(&m_jit);
888
889 setResultAndResetStack();
890
891 m_jit.addJSDirectCall(slowPath, callLinkInfo);
892 return;
893 }
894
895 m_jit.emitStoreCallSiteIndex(callSite);
896
897 CCallHelpers::JumpList slowCases;
898 if (isTail) {
899 slowCases = callLinkInfo->emitTailCallFastPath(m_jit, calleeGPR, InvalidGPRReg, CallLinkInfo::UseDataIC::No, [&] {
900 if (node->op() == TailCall) {
901 callLinkInfo->setFrameShuffleData(shuffleData);
902 CallFrameShuffler(m_jit, shuffleData).prepareForTailCall();
903 } else {
904 m_jit.emitRestoreCalleeSaves();
905 m_jit.prepareForTailCallSlow();
906 }
907 });
908 } else
909 slowCases = callLinkInfo->emitFastPath(m_jit, calleeGPR, InvalidGPRReg, CallLinkInfo::UseDataIC::No);
910 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.jump();
911
912 slowCases.link(&m_jit);
913 auto slowPathStart = m_jit.label();
914
915 if (node->op() == TailCall) {
916 CallFrameShuffler callFrameShuffler(m_jit, shuffleData);
917 callFrameShuffler.setCalleeJSValueRegs(JSValueRegs(GPRInfo::regT0));
918 callFrameShuffler.prepareForSlowPath();
919 } else {
920 m_jit.move(calleeGPR, GPRInfo::regT0); // Callee needs to be in regT0
921 if (isTail)
922 m_jit.emitRestoreCalleeSaves(); // This needs to happen after we moved calleeGPR to regT0
923 }
924
925 m_jit.move(TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, globalObject), GPRInfo::regT3); // JSGlobalObject needs to be in regT3
926 callLinkInfo->emitSlowPath(vm(), m_jit);
927
928 done.link(&m_jit);
929 auto doneLocation = m_jit.label();
930
931 if (isTail)
932 m_jit.abortWithReason(JITDidReturnFromTailCall);
933 else
934 setResultAndResetStack();
935
936 m_jit.addJSCall(slowPathStart, doneLocation, callLinkInfo);
937}
938
939// Clang should allow unreachable [[clang::fallthrough]] in template functions if any template expansion uses it
940// http://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=18619
941IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("implicit-fallthrough")
942template<bool strict>
943GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateInt32Internal(Edge edge, DataFormat& returnFormat)
944{
945 AbstractValue& value = m_state.forNode(edge);
946 SpeculatedType type = value.m_type;
947 ASSERT(edge.useKind() != KnownInt32Use || !(value.m_type & ~SpecInt32Only));
948
949 m_interpreter.filter(value, SpecInt32Only);
950 if (value.isClear()) {
951 if (mayHaveTypeCheck(edge.useKind()))
952 terminateSpeculativeExecution(Uncountable, JSValueRegs(), nullptr);
953 returnFormat = DataFormatInt32;
954 return allocate();
955 }
956
957 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = edge->virtualRegister();
958 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
959
960 switch (info.registerFormat()) {
961 case DataFormatNone: {
962 GPRReg gpr = allocate();
963
964 if (edge->hasConstant()) {
965 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderConstant);
966 ASSERT(edge->isInt32Constant());
967 m_jit.move(MacroAssembler::Imm32(edge->asInt32()), gpr);
968 info.fillInt32(*m_stream, gpr);
969 returnFormat = DataFormatInt32;
970 return gpr;
971 }
972
973 DataFormat spillFormat = info.spillFormat();
974
975 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, (spillFormat & DataFormatJS) || spillFormat == DataFormatInt32, spillFormat);
976
977 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderSpilled);
978
979 if (spillFormat == DataFormatJSInt32 || spillFormat == DataFormatInt32) {
980 // If we know this was spilled as an integer we can fill without checking.
981 if (strict) {
982 m_jit.load32(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
983 info.fillInt32(*m_stream, gpr);
984 returnFormat = DataFormatInt32;
985 return gpr;
986 }
987 if (spillFormat == DataFormatInt32) {
988 m_jit.load32(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
989 info.fillInt32(*m_stream, gpr);
990 returnFormat = DataFormatInt32;
991 } else {
992 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
993 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSInt32);
994 returnFormat = DataFormatJSInt32;
995 }
996 return gpr;
997 }
998 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
999
1000 // Fill as JSValue, and fall through.
1001 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSInt32);
1002 m_gprs.unlock(gpr);
1003 FALLTHROUGH;
1004 }
1005
1006 case DataFormatJS: {
1007 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, !(type & SpecInt52Any));
1008 // Check the value is an integer.
1009 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1010 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1011 if (type & ~SpecInt32Only)
1012 speculationCheck(BadType, JSValueRegs(gpr), edge, m_jit.branchIfNotInt32(gpr));
1013 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSInt32);
1014 // If !strict we're done, return.
1015 if (!strict) {
1016 returnFormat = DataFormatJSInt32;
1017 return gpr;
1018 }
1019 // else fall through & handle as DataFormatJSInt32.
1020 m_gprs.unlock(gpr);
1021 FALLTHROUGH;
1022 }
1023
1024 case DataFormatJSInt32: {
1025 // In a strict fill we need to strip off the value tag.
1026 if (strict) {
1027 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1028 GPRReg result;
1029 // If the register has already been locked we need to take a copy.
1030 // If not, we'll zero extend in place, so mark on the info that this is now type DataFormatInt32, not DataFormatJSInt32.
1031 if (m_gprs.isLocked(gpr))
1032 result = allocate();
1033 else {
1034 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1035 info.fillInt32(*m_stream, gpr);
1036 result = gpr;
1037 }
1038 m_jit.zeroExtend32ToWord(gpr, result);
1039 returnFormat = DataFormatInt32;
1040 return result;
1041 }
1042
1043 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1044 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1045 returnFormat = DataFormatJSInt32;
1046 return gpr;
1047 }
1048
1049 case DataFormatInt32: {
1050 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1051 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1052 returnFormat = DataFormatInt32;
1053 return gpr;
1054 }
1055
1056 case DataFormatJSDouble:
1057 case DataFormatCell:
1058 case DataFormatBoolean:
1059 case DataFormatJSCell:
1060 case DataFormatJSBoolean:
1061 case DataFormatDouble:
1062 case DataFormatStorage:
1063 case DataFormatInt52:
1064 case DataFormatStrictInt52:
1065 case DataFormatBigInt32:
1066 case DataFormatJSBigInt32:
1067 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Bad data format");
1068
1069 default:
1070 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Corrupt data format");
1071 return InvalidGPRReg;
1072 }
1073}
1074IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1075
1076GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateInt32(Edge edge, DataFormat& returnFormat)
1077{
1078 return fillSpeculateInt32Internal<false>(edge, returnFormat);
1079}
1080
1081GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateInt32Strict(Edge edge)
1082{
1083 DataFormat mustBeDataFormatInt32;
1084 GPRReg result = fillSpeculateInt32Internal<true>(edge, mustBeDataFormatInt32);
1085 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, mustBeDataFormatInt32 == DataFormatInt32, mustBeDataFormatInt32);
1086 return result;
1087}
1088
1089GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateInt52(Edge edge, DataFormat desiredFormat)
1090{
1091 ASSERT(desiredFormat == DataFormatInt52 || desiredFormat == DataFormatStrictInt52);
1092 AbstractValue& value = m_state.forNode(edge);
1093
1094 m_interpreter.filter(value, SpecInt52Any);
1095 if (value.isClear()) {
1096 if (mayHaveTypeCheck(edge.useKind()))
1097 terminateSpeculativeExecution(Uncountable, JSValueRegs(), nullptr);
1098 return allocate();
1099 }
1100
1101 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = edge->virtualRegister();
1102 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
1103
1104 switch (info.registerFormat()) {
1105 case DataFormatNone: {
1106 GPRReg gpr = allocate();
1107
1108 if (edge->hasConstant()) {
1109 JSValue jsValue = edge->asJSValue();
1110 ASSERT(jsValue.isAnyInt());
1111 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderConstant);
1112 int64_t value = jsValue.asAnyInt();
1113 if (desiredFormat == DataFormatInt52)
1114 value = value << JSValue::int52ShiftAmount;
1115 m_jit.move(MacroAssembler::Imm64(value), gpr);
1116 info.fillGPR(*m_stream, gpr, desiredFormat);
1117 return gpr;
1118 }
1119
1120 DataFormat spillFormat = info.spillFormat();
1121
1122 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, spillFormat == DataFormatInt52 || spillFormat == DataFormatStrictInt52, spillFormat);
1123
1124 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderSpilled);
1125
1126 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
1127 if (desiredFormat == DataFormatStrictInt52) {
1128 if (spillFormat == DataFormatInt52)
1129 m_jit.rshift64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::int52ShiftAmount), gpr);
1130 info.fillStrictInt52(*m_stream, gpr);
1131 return gpr;
1132 }
1133 if (spillFormat == DataFormatStrictInt52)
1134 m_jit.lshift64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::int52ShiftAmount), gpr);
1135 info.fillInt52(*m_stream, gpr);
1136 return gpr;
1137 }
1138
1139 case DataFormatStrictInt52: {
1140 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1141 bool wasLocked = m_gprs.isLocked(gpr);
1142 lock(gpr);
1143 if (desiredFormat == DataFormatStrictInt52)
1144 return gpr;
1145 if (wasLocked) {
1146 GPRReg result = allocate();
1147 m_jit.move(gpr, result);
1148 unlock(gpr);
1149 gpr = result;
1150 } else
1151 info.fillInt52(*m_stream, gpr);
1152 m_jit.lshift64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::int52ShiftAmount), gpr);
1153 return gpr;
1154 }
1155
1156 case DataFormatInt52: {
1157 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1158 bool wasLocked = m_gprs.isLocked(gpr);
1159 lock(gpr);
1160 if (desiredFormat == DataFormatInt52)
1161 return gpr;
1162 if (wasLocked) {
1163 GPRReg result = allocate();
1164 m_jit.move(gpr, result);
1165 unlock(gpr);
1166 gpr = result;
1167 } else
1168 info.fillStrictInt52(*m_stream, gpr);
1169 m_jit.rshift64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::int52ShiftAmount), gpr);
1170 return gpr;
1171 }
1172
1173 default:
1174 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Bad data format");
1175 return InvalidGPRReg;
1176 }
1177}
1178
1179FPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateDouble(Edge edge)
1180{
1181 ASSERT(edge.useKind() == DoubleRepUse || edge.useKind() == DoubleRepRealUse || edge.useKind() == DoubleRepAnyIntUse);
1182 ASSERT(edge->hasDoubleResult());
1183 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = edge->virtualRegister();
1184 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
1185
1186 if (info.registerFormat() == DataFormatNone) {
1187 if (edge->hasConstant()) {
1188 if (edge->isNumberConstant()) {
1189 FPRReg fpr = fprAllocate();
1190 int64_t doubleAsInt = reinterpretDoubleToInt64(edge->asNumber());
1191 if (!doubleAsInt)
1192 m_jit.moveZeroToDouble(fpr);
1193 else {
1194 GPRReg gpr = allocate();
1195 m_jit.move(MacroAssembler::Imm64(doubleAsInt), gpr);
1196 m_jit.move64ToDouble(gpr, fpr);
1197 unlock(gpr);
1198 }
1199
1200 m_fprs.retain(fpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderDouble);
1201 info.fillDouble(*m_stream, fpr);
1202 return fpr;
1203 }
1204 if (mayHaveTypeCheck(edge.useKind()))
1205 terminateSpeculativeExecution(Uncountable, JSValueRegs(), nullptr);
1206 return fprAllocate();
1207 }
1208
1209 DataFormat spillFormat = info.spillFormat();
1210 if (spillFormat != DataFormatDouble) {
1211 DFG_CRASH(
1212 m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, toCString(
1213 "Expected ", edge, " to have double format but instead it is spilled as ",
1214 dataFormatToString(spillFormat)).data());
1215 }
1216 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, spillFormat == DataFormatDouble, spillFormat);
1217 FPRReg fpr = fprAllocate();
1218 m_jit.loadDouble(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), fpr);
1219 m_fprs.retain(fpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderDouble);
1220 info.fillDouble(*m_stream, fpr);
1221 return fpr;
1222 }
1223
1224 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, info.registerFormat() == DataFormatDouble, info.registerFormat());
1225 FPRReg fpr = info.fpr();
1226 m_fprs.lock(fpr);
1227 return fpr;
1228}
1229
1230GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateCell(Edge edge)
1231{
1232 AbstractValue& value = m_state.forNode(edge);
1233 SpeculatedType type = value.m_type;
1234 ASSERT((edge.useKind() != KnownCellUse && edge.useKind() != KnownStringUse) || !(value.m_type & ~SpecCellCheck));
1235
1236 m_interpreter.filter(value, SpecCellCheck);
1237 if (value.isClear()) {
1238 if (mayHaveTypeCheck(edge.useKind()))
1239 terminateSpeculativeExecution(Uncountable, JSValueRegs(), nullptr);
1240 return allocate();
1241 }
1242
1243 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = edge->virtualRegister();
1244 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
1245
1246 switch (info.registerFormat()) {
1247 // FIXME: some of these cases look like they could share code.
1248 // Look at fillSpeculateInt32Internal for an example.
1249 case DataFormatNone: {
1250 GPRReg gpr = allocate();
1251
1252 if (edge->hasConstant()) {
1253 JSValue jsValue = edge->asJSValue();
1254 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderConstant);
1255 m_jit.move(MacroAssembler::TrustedImm64(JSValue::encode(jsValue)), gpr);
1256 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSCell);
1257 return gpr;
1258 }
1259
1260 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderSpilled);
1261 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
1262
1263 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJS);
1264 if (type & ~SpecCellCheck)
1265 speculationCheck(BadType, JSValueRegs(gpr), edge, m_jit.branchIfNotCell(JSValueRegs(gpr)));
1266 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSCell);
1267 return gpr;
1268 }
1269
1270 case DataFormatCell:
1271 case DataFormatJSCell: {
1272 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1273 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1274 if (ASSERT_ENABLED) {
1275 MacroAssembler::Jump checkCell = m_jit.branchIfCell(JSValueRegs(gpr));
1276 m_jit.abortWithReason(DFGIsNotCell);
1277 checkCell.link(&m_jit);
1278 }
1279 return gpr;
1280 }
1281
1282 case DataFormatJS: {
1283 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1284 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1285 if (type & ~SpecCellCheck)
1286 speculationCheck(BadType, JSValueRegs(gpr), edge, m_jit.branchIfNotCell(JSValueRegs(gpr)));
1287 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSCell);
1288 return gpr;
1289 }
1290
1291 case DataFormatJSInt32:
1292 case DataFormatInt32:
1293 case DataFormatJSDouble:
1294 case DataFormatJSBoolean:
1295 case DataFormatBoolean:
1296 case DataFormatDouble:
1297 case DataFormatStorage:
1298 case DataFormatInt52:
1299 case DataFormatStrictInt52:
1300 case DataFormatBigInt32:
1301 case DataFormatJSBigInt32:
1302 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Bad data format");
1303
1304 default:
1305 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Corrupt data format");
1306 return InvalidGPRReg;
1307 }
1308}
1309
1310GPRReg SpeculativeJIT::fillSpeculateBoolean(Edge edge)
1311{
1312 AbstractValue& value = m_state.forNode(edge);
1313 SpeculatedType type = value.m_type;
1314 ASSERT(edge.useKind() != KnownBooleanUse || !(value.m_type & ~SpecBoolean));
1315
1316 m_interpreter.filter(value, SpecBoolean);
1317 if (value.isClear()) {
1318 if (mayHaveTypeCheck(edge.useKind()))
1319 terminateSpeculativeExecution(Uncountable, JSValueRegs(), nullptr);
1320 return allocate();
1321 }
1322
1323 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = edge->virtualRegister();
1324 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
1325
1326 switch (info.registerFormat()) {
1327 case DataFormatNone: {
1328 GPRReg gpr = allocate();
1329
1330 if (edge->hasConstant()) {
1331 JSValue jsValue = edge->asJSValue();
1332 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderConstant);
1333 m_jit.move(MacroAssembler::TrustedImm64(JSValue::encode(jsValue)), gpr);
1334 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSBoolean);
1335 return gpr;
1336 }
1337 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, info.spillFormat() & DataFormatJS, info.spillFormat());
1338 m_gprs.retain(gpr, virtualRegister, SpillOrderSpilled);
1339 m_jit.load64(JITCompiler::addressFor(virtualRegister), gpr);
1340
1341 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJS);
1342 if (type & ~SpecBoolean) {
1343 m_jit.xor64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), gpr);
1344 speculationCheck(BadType, JSValueRegs(gpr), edge, m_jit.branchTest64(MacroAssembler::NonZero, gpr, TrustedImm32(static_cast<int32_t>(~1))), SpeculationRecovery(BooleanSpeculationCheck, gpr, InvalidGPRReg));
1345 m_jit.xor64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), gpr);
1346 }
1347 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSBoolean);
1348 return gpr;
1349 }
1350
1351 case DataFormatBoolean:
1352 case DataFormatJSBoolean: {
1353 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1354 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1355 return gpr;
1356 }
1357
1358 case DataFormatJS: {
1359 GPRReg gpr = info.gpr();
1360 m_gprs.lock(gpr);
1361 if (type & ~SpecBoolean) {
1362 m_jit.xor64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), gpr);
1363 speculationCheck(BadType, JSValueRegs(gpr), edge, m_jit.branchTest64(MacroAssembler::NonZero, gpr, TrustedImm32(static_cast<int32_t>(~1))), SpeculationRecovery(BooleanSpeculationCheck, gpr, InvalidGPRReg));
1364 m_jit.xor64(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), gpr);
1365 }
1366 info.fillJSValue(*m_stream, gpr, DataFormatJSBoolean);
1367 return gpr;
1368 }
1369
1370 case DataFormatJSInt32:
1371 case DataFormatInt32:
1372 case DataFormatJSDouble:
1373 case DataFormatJSCell:
1374 case DataFormatCell:
1375 case DataFormatDouble:
1376 case DataFormatStorage:
1377 case DataFormatInt52:
1378 case DataFormatStrictInt52:
1379 case DataFormatBigInt32:
1380 case DataFormatJSBigInt32:
1381 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Bad data format");
1382
1383 default:
1384 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), m_currentNode, "Corrupt data format");
1385 return InvalidGPRReg;
1386 }
1387}
