5608 };
5609
5610 if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::False)
5611 emitBigEndianCode();
5612 else if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::True)
5613 emitLittleEndianCode();
5614 else {
5615 RELEASE_ASSERT(isLittleEndianGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
5616 auto isBigEndian = m_jit.branchTest32(MacroAssembler::Zero, isLittleEndianGPR, TrustedImm32(1));
5617 emitLittleEndianCode();
5618 auto done = m_jit.jump();
5619 isBigEndian.link(&m_jit);
5620 emitBigEndianCode();
5621 done.link(&m_jit);
5622 }
5623 } else {
5624 RELEASE_ASSERT(data.byteSize == 8);
5625 RELEASE_ASSERT(valueFPR != InvalidFPRReg);
5626
5627 auto emitLittleEndianCode = [&] {
5628 m_jit.storeDouble(valueFPR, baseIndex);
5629 };
5630 auto emitBigEndianCode = [&] {
5631 m_jit.moveDoubleTo64(valueFPR, t3);
5632 m_jit.byteSwap64(t3);
5633 m_jit.store64(t3, baseIndex);
5634 };
5635
5636 if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::False)
5637 emitBigEndianCode();
5638 else if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::True)
5639 emitLittleEndianCode();
5640 else {
5641 RELEASE_ASSERT(isLittleEndianGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
5642 auto isBigEndian = m_jit.branchTest32(MacroAssembler::Zero, isLittleEndianGPR, TrustedImm32(1));
5643 emitLittleEndianCode();
5644 auto done = m_jit.jump();
5645 isBigEndian.link(&m_jit);
5646 emitBigEndianCode();
5647 done.link(&m_jit);
5648 }
5649 }
5650 } else {
5651 switch (data.byteSize) {
5652 case 1:
5653 RELEASE_ASSERT(valueEdge.useKind() == Int32Use);
5654 RELEASE_ASSERT(valueGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
5655 m_jit.store8(valueGPR, baseIndex);
5656 break;
5657 case 2: {
5658 RELEASE_ASSERT(valueEdge.useKind() == Int32Use);
5659 RELEASE_ASSERT(valueGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
5660
5661 auto emitLittleEndianCode = [&] {
5662 m_jit.store16(valueGPR, baseIndex);
5663 };
5664 auto emitBigEndianCode = [&] {
5665 m_jit.move(valueGPR, t3);
5666 m_jit.byteSwap16(t3);
5667 m_jit.store16(t3, baseIndex);
5668 };
5669
5670 if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::False)
5671 emitBigEndianCode();
5672 else if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::True)
5673 emitLittleEndianCode();
5674 else {
5675 RELEASE_ASSERT(isLittleEndianGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
5676 auto isBigEndian = m_jit.branchTest32(MacroAssembler::Zero, isLittleEndianGPR, TrustedImm32(1));
5677 emitLittleEndianCode();
5678 auto done = m_jit.jump();
5679 isBigEndian.link(&m_jit);
5680 emitBigEndianCode();
5681 done.link(&m_jit);
5682 }
5683 break;
5684 }
5685 case 4: {
5686 RELEASE_ASSERT(valueEdge.useKind() == Int32Use || valueEdge.useKind() == Int52RepUse);
5687
5688 auto emitLittleEndianCode = [&] {
5689 m_jit.store32(valueGPR, baseIndex);
5690 };
5691
5692 auto emitBigEndianCode = [&] {
5693 m_jit.zeroExtend32ToWord(valueGPR, t3);
5694 m_jit.byteSwap32(t3);
5695 m_jit.store32(t3, baseIndex);
5696 };
5697
5698 if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::False)
5699 emitBigEndianCode();
5700 else if (data.isLittleEndian == TriState::True)
5701 emitLittleEndianCode();
5702 else {
5703 RELEASE_ASSERT(isLittleEndianGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
5704 auto isBigEndian = m_jit.branchTest32(MacroAssembler::Zero, isLittleEndianGPR, TrustedImm32(1));
5705 emitLittleEndianCode();
5706 auto done = m_jit.jump();
5707 isBigEndian.link(&m_jit);
5708 emitBigEndianCode();
5709 done.link(&m_jit);
5710 }
5711
5712 break;
5713 }
5714 default:
5715 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5716 }
5717 }
5718
5719 noResult(node);
5720 break;
5721 }
5722
5723#if ENABLE(FTL_JIT)
5724 case CheckTierUpInLoop: {
5725 MacroAssembler::Jump callTierUp = m_jit.branchAdd32(
5726 MacroAssembler::PositiveOrZero,
5727 TrustedImm32(Options::ftlTierUpCounterIncrementForLoop()),
5728 MacroAssembler::AbsoluteAddress(&m_jit.jitCode()->tierUpCounter.m_counter));
5729
5730 MacroAssembler::Label toNextOperation = m_jit.label();
5731
5732 Vector<SilentRegisterSavePlan> savePlans;
5733 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(false, savePlans, InvalidGPRReg);
5734 BytecodeIndex bytecodeIndex = node->origin.semantic.bytecodeIndex();
5735
5736 addSlowPathGeneratorLambda([=]() {
5737 callTierUp.link(&m_jit);
5738
5739 silentSpill(savePlans);
5740 callOperation(operationTriggerTierUpNowInLoop, &vm(), TrustedImm32(bytecodeIndex.asBits()));
5741 silentFill(savePlans);
5742
5743 m_jit.jump().linkTo(toNextOperation, &m_jit);
5744 });
5745 break;
5746 }
5747
5748 case CheckTierUpAtReturn: {
5749 MacroAssembler::Jump done = m_jit.branchAdd32(
5750 MacroAssembler::Signed,
5751 TrustedImm32(Options::ftlTierUpCounterIncrementForReturn()),
5752 MacroAssembler::AbsoluteAddress(&m_jit.jitCode()->tierUpCounter.m_counter));
5753
5754 silentSpillAllRegisters(InvalidGPRReg);
5755 callOperation(operationTriggerTierUpNow, &vm());
5756 silentFillAllRegisters();
5757
5758 done.link(&m_jit);
5759 break;
5760 }
5761
5762 case CheckTierUpAndOSREnter: {
5763 ASSERT(!node->origin.semantic.inlineCallFrame());
5764
5765 GPRTemporary temp(this);
5766 GPRReg tempGPR = temp.gpr();
5767
5768 BytecodeIndex bytecodeIndex = node->origin.semantic.bytecodeIndex();
5769 auto triggerIterator = m_jit.jitCode()->tierUpEntryTriggers.find(bytecodeIndex);
5770 DFG_ASSERT(m_jit.graph(), node, triggerIterator != m_jit.jitCode()->tierUpEntryTriggers.end());
5771 JITCode::TriggerReason* forceEntryTrigger = &(m_jit.jitCode()->tierUpEntryTriggers.find(bytecodeIndex)->value);
5772 static_assert(!static_cast<uint8_t>(JITCode::TriggerReason::DontTrigger), "the JIT code assumes non-zero means 'enter'");
5773 static_assert(sizeof(JITCode::TriggerReason) == 1, "branchTest8 assumes this size");
5774
5775 MacroAssembler::Jump forceOSREntry = m_jit.branchTest8(MacroAssembler::NonZero, MacroAssembler::AbsoluteAddress(forceEntryTrigger));
5776 MacroAssembler::Jump overflowedCounter = m_jit.branchAdd32(
5777 MacroAssembler::PositiveOrZero,
5778 TrustedImm32(Options::ftlTierUpCounterIncrementForLoop()),
5779 MacroAssembler::AbsoluteAddress(&m_jit.jitCode()->tierUpCounter.m_counter));
5780 MacroAssembler::Label toNextOperation = m_jit.label();
5781
5782 Vector<SilentRegisterSavePlan> savePlans;
5783 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(false, savePlans, tempGPR);
5784
5785 unsigned streamIndex = m_stream->size();
5786 m_jit.jitCode()->bytecodeIndexToStreamIndex.add(bytecodeIndex, streamIndex);
5787
5788 addSlowPathGeneratorLambda([=]() {
5789 forceOSREntry.link(&m_jit);
5790 overflowedCounter.link(&m_jit);
5791
5792 silentSpill(savePlans);
5793 callOperation(operationTriggerOSREntryNow, tempGPR, &vm(), TrustedImm32(bytecodeIndex.asBits()));
5794
5795 if (savePlans.isEmpty())
5796 m_jit.branchTestPtr(MacroAssembler::Zero, tempGPR).linkTo(toNextOperation, &m_jit);
5797 else {
5798 MacroAssembler::Jump osrEnter = m_jit.branchTestPtr(MacroAssembler::NonZero, tempGPR);
5799 silentFill(savePlans);
5800 m_jit.jump().linkTo(toNextOperation, &m_jit);
5801 osrEnter.link(&m_jit);
5802 }
5803 m_jit.emitRestoreCalleeSaves();
5804 m_jit.farJump(tempGPR, GPRInfo::callFrameRegister);
5805 });
5806 break;
5807 }
5808
5809#else // ENABLE(FTL_JIT)
5810 case CheckTierUpInLoop:
5811 case CheckTierUpAtReturn:
5812 case CheckTierUpAndOSREnter:
5813 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), node, "Unexpected tier-up node");
5814 break;
5815#endif // ENABLE(FTL_JIT)
5816
5817 case FilterCallLinkStatus:
5818 case FilterGetByStatus:
5819 case FilterPutByIdStatus:
5820 case FilterInByStatus:
5821 case FilterDeleteByStatus:
5822 case FilterCheckPrivateBrandStatus:
5823 case FilterSetPrivateBrandStatus:
5824 m_interpreter.filterICStatus(node);
5825 noResult(node);
5826 break;
5827
5828 case LastNodeType:
5829 case EntrySwitch:
5830 case InitializeEntrypointArguments:
5831 case Phi:
5832 case Upsilon:
5833 case ExtractOSREntryLocal:
5834 case AssertInBounds:
5835 case CheckInBounds:
5836 case ArithIMul:
5837 case MultiGetByOffset:
5838 case MultiPutByOffset:
5839 case MultiDeleteByOffset:
5840 case FiatInt52:
5841 case CheckBadValue:
5842 case BottomValue:
5843 case PhantomNewObject:
5844 case PhantomNewFunction:
5845 case PhantomNewGeneratorFunction:
5846 case PhantomNewAsyncFunction:
5847 case PhantomNewAsyncGeneratorFunction:
5848 case PhantomNewInternalFieldObject:
5849 case PhantomCreateActivation:
5850 case PhantomNewRegexp:
5851 case GetMyArgumentByVal:
5852 case GetMyArgumentByValOutOfBounds:
5853 case GetVectorLength:
5854 case PutHint:
5855 case CheckStructureImmediate:
5856 case MaterializeCreateActivation:
5857 case MaterializeNewInternalFieldObject:
5858 case PutStack:
5859 case KillStack:
5860 case GetStack:
5861 case PhantomCreateRest:
5862 case PhantomSpread:
5863 case PhantomNewArrayWithSpread:
5864 case PhantomNewArrayBuffer:
5865 case IdentityWithProfile:
5866 case CPUIntrinsic:
5867 DFG_CRASH(m_jit.graph(), node, "Unexpected node");
5868 break;
5869 }
5870
5871 if (!m_compileOkay)
5872 return;
5873
5874 if (node->hasResult() && node->mustGenerate())
5875 use(node);
5876}

5878void SpeculativeJIT::moveTrueTo(GPRReg gpr)
5879{
5880 m_jit.move(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueTrue), gpr);
5881}
5882
5883void SpeculativeJIT::moveFalseTo(GPRReg gpr)
5884{
5885 m_jit.move(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), gpr);
5886}
5887
5888void SpeculativeJIT::blessBoolean(GPRReg gpr)
5889{
5890 m_jit.or32(TrustedImm32(JSValue::ValueFalse), gpr);
5891}
5892
5893void SpeculativeJIT::convertAnyInt(Edge valueEdge, GPRReg resultGPR)
5894{
5895 JSValueOperand value(this, valueEdge, ManualOperandSpeculation);
5896 GPRReg valueGPR = value.gpr();
5897
5898 JITCompiler::Jump notInt32 = m_jit.branchIfNotInt32(valueGPR);
5899
5900 m_jit.signExtend32ToPtr(valueGPR, resultGPR);
5901 JITCompiler::Jump done = m_jit.jump();
5902
5903 notInt32.link(&m_jit);
5904 silentSpillAllRegisters(resultGPR);
5905 callOperation(operationConvertBoxedDoubleToInt52, resultGPR, valueGPR);
5906 silentFillAllRegisters();
5907
5908 DFG_TYPE_CHECK(
5909 JSValueRegs(valueGPR), valueEdge, SpecInt32Only | SpecAnyIntAsDouble,
5910 m_jit.branch64(
5911 JITCompiler::Equal, resultGPR,
5912 JITCompiler::TrustedImm64(JSValue::notInt52)));
5913 done.link(&m_jit);
5914}
5915
5916void SpeculativeJIT::speculateAnyInt(Edge edge)
5917{
5918 if (!needsTypeCheck(edge, SpecInt32Only | SpecAnyIntAsDouble))
5919 return;
5920
5921 GPRTemporary temp(this);
5922 convertAnyInt(edge, temp.gpr());
5923}
5924
5925void SpeculativeJIT::speculateInt32(Edge edge, JSValueRegs regs)
5926{
5927 DFG_TYPE_CHECK(regs, edge, SpecInt32Only, m_jit.branchIfNotInt32(regs));
5928}
5929
5930void SpeculativeJIT::speculateDoubleRepAnyInt(Edge edge)
5931{
5932 if (!needsTypeCheck(edge, SpecAnyIntAsDouble))
5933 return;
5934
5935 SpeculateDoubleOperand value(this, edge);
5936 FPRReg valueFPR = value.fpr();
5937
5938 flushRegisters();
5939 GPRFlushedCallResult result(this);
5940 GPRReg resultGPR = result.gpr();
5941 callOperation(operationConvertDoubleToInt52, resultGPR, valueFPR);
5942
5943 DFG_TYPE_CHECK(
5944 JSValueRegs(), edge, SpecAnyIntAsDouble,
5945 m_jit.branch64(
5946 JITCompiler::Equal, resultGPR,
5947 JITCompiler::TrustedImm64(JSValue::notInt52)));
5948}

5950void SpeculativeJIT::compileArithRandom(Node* node)
5951{
5952 JSGlobalObject* globalObject = m_jit.graph().globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic);
5953 GPRTemporary temp1(this);
5954 GPRTemporary temp2(this);
5955 GPRTemporary temp3(this);
5956 FPRTemporary result(this);
5957 m_jit.emitRandomThunk(globalObject, temp1.gpr(), temp2.gpr(), temp3.gpr(), result.fpr());
5958 doubleResult(result.fpr(), node);
5959}
5960
5961void SpeculativeJIT::compileStringCodePointAt(Node* node)
5962{
5963 // We emit CheckArray on this node as we do in StringCharCodeAt node so that we do not need to check SpecString here.
5964 // And CheckArray also ensures that this String is not a rope.
5965 SpeculateCellOperand string(this, node->child1());
5966 SpeculateStrictInt32Operand index(this, node->child2());
5967 StorageOperand storage(this, node->child3());
5968 GPRTemporary scratch1(this);
5969 GPRTemporary scratch2(this);
5970 GPRTemporary scratch3(this);
5971
5972 GPRReg stringGPR = string.gpr();
5973 GPRReg indexGPR = index.gpr();
5974 GPRReg storageGPR = storage.gpr();
5975 GPRReg scratch1GPR = scratch1.gpr();
5976 GPRReg scratch2GPR = scratch2.gpr();
5977 GPRReg scratch3GPR = scratch3.gpr();
5978
5979 m_jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(stringGPR, JSString::offsetOfValue()), scratch1GPR);
5980 m_jit.load32(CCallHelpers::Address(scratch1GPR, StringImpl::lengthMemoryOffset()), scratch2GPR);
5981
5982 // unsigned comparison so we can filter out negative indices and indices that are too large
5983 speculationCheck(Uncountable, JSValueRegs(), nullptr, m_jit.branch32(CCallHelpers::AboveOrEqual, indexGPR, scratch2GPR));
5984
5985 // Load the character into scratch1GPR
5986 auto is16Bit = m_jit.branchTest32(CCallHelpers::Zero, CCallHelpers::Address(scratch1GPR, StringImpl::flagsOffset()), TrustedImm32(StringImpl::flagIs8Bit()));
5987
5988 CCallHelpers::JumpList done;
5989
5990 m_jit.load8(CCallHelpers::BaseIndex(storageGPR, indexGPR, CCallHelpers::TimesOne, 0), scratch1GPR);
5991 done.append(m_jit.jump());
5992
5993 is16Bit.link(&m_jit);
5994 m_jit.load16(CCallHelpers::BaseIndex(storageGPR, indexGPR, CCallHelpers::TimesTwo, 0), scratch1GPR);
5995 // This is ok. indexGPR must be positive int32_t here and adding 1 never causes overflow if we treat indexGPR as uint32_t.
5996 m_jit.add32(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(1), indexGPR, scratch3GPR);
5997 done.append(m_jit.branch32(CCallHelpers::AboveOrEqual, scratch3GPR, scratch2GPR));
5998 m_jit.and32(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(0xfffffc00), scratch1GPR, scratch2GPR);
5999 done.append(m_jit.branch32(CCallHelpers::NotEqual, scratch2GPR, CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(0xd800)));
6000 m_jit.load16(CCallHelpers::BaseIndex(storageGPR, scratch3GPR, CCallHelpers::TimesTwo, 0), scratch3GPR);
6001 m_jit.and32(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(0xfffffc00), scratch3GPR, scratch2GPR);
6002 done.append(m_jit.branch32(CCallHelpers::NotEqual, scratch2GPR, CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(0xdc00)));
6003 m_jit.lshift32(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(10), scratch1GPR);
6004 m_jit.getEffectiveAddress(CCallHelpers::BaseIndex(scratch1GPR, scratch3GPR, CCallHelpers::TimesOne, -U16_SURROGATE_OFFSET), scratch1GPR);
6005 done.link(&m_jit);
6006
6007 strictInt32Result(scratch1GPR, m_currentNode);
6008}
6009
6010void SpeculativeJIT::compileDateGet(Node* node)
6011{
6012 SpeculateCellOperand base(this, node->child1());
6013 GPRReg baseGPR = base.gpr();
6014 speculateDateObject(node->child1(), baseGPR);
6015
6016 auto emitGetCodeWithCallback = [&] (ptrdiff_t cachedDoubleOffset, ptrdiff_t cachedDataOffset, auto* operation, auto callback) {
6017 JSValueRegsTemporary result(this);
6018 FPRTemporary temp1(this);
6019 FPRTemporary temp2(this);
6020
6021 JSValueRegs resultRegs = result.regs();
6022 FPRReg temp1FPR = temp1.fpr();
6023 FPRReg temp2FPR = temp2.fpr();
6024
6025 CCallHelpers::JumpList slowCases;
6026
6027 m_jit.loadPtr(CCallHelpers::Address(baseGPR, DateInstance::offsetOfData()), resultRegs.payloadGPR());
6028 slowCases.append(m_jit.branchTestPtr(CCallHelpers::Zero, resultRegs.payloadGPR()));
6029 m_jit.loadDouble(CCallHelpers::Address(baseGPR, DateInstance::offsetOfInternalNumber()), temp1FPR);
6030 m_jit.loadDouble(CCallHelpers::Address(resultRegs.payloadGPR(), cachedDoubleOffset), temp2FPR);
6031 slowCases.append(m_jit.branchDouble(CCallHelpers::DoubleNotEqualOrUnordered, temp1FPR, temp2FPR));
6032 m_jit.load32(CCallHelpers::Address(resultRegs.payloadGPR(), cachedDataOffset), resultRegs.payloadGPR());
6033 callback(resultRegs.payloadGPR());
6034 m_jit.boxInt32(resultRegs.payloadGPR(), resultRegs);
6035
6036 addSlowPathGenerator(slowPathCall(slowCases, this, operation, NeedToSpill, ExceptionCheckRequirement::CheckNotNeeded, resultRegs, &vm(), baseGPR));
6037
6038 jsValueResult(resultRegs, node);
6039 };
6040
6041 auto emitGetCode = [&] (ptrdiff_t cachedDoubleOffset, ptrdiff_t cachedDataOffset, auto* operation) {
6042 emitGetCodeWithCallback(cachedDoubleOffset, cachedDataOffset, operation, [] (GPRReg) { });
6043 };
6044
6045 switch (node->intrinsic()) {
6046 case DatePrototypeGetTimeIntrinsic: {
6047 FPRTemporary result(this);
6048 FPRReg resultFPR = result.fpr();
6049 m_jit.loadDouble(CCallHelpers::Address(baseGPR, DateInstance::offsetOfInternalNumber()), resultFPR);
6050 doubleResult(resultFPR, node);
6051 break;
6052 }
6053
6054 // We do not have any timezone offset which affects on milliseconds.
6055 // So Date#getMilliseconds and Date#getUTCMilliseconds have the same implementation.
6056 case DatePrototypeGetMillisecondsIntrinsic:
6057 case DatePrototypeGetUTCMillisecondsIntrinsic: {
6058 JSValueRegsTemporary result(this);
6059 FPRTemporary temp1(this);
6060 FPRTemporary temp2(this);
6061 FPRTemporary temp3(this);
6062 JSValueRegs resultRegs = result.regs();
6063 FPRReg temp1FPR = temp1.fpr();
6064 FPRReg temp2FPR = temp2.fpr();
6065 FPRReg temp3FPR = temp3.fpr();
6066
6067 m_jit.moveTrustedValue(jsNaN(), resultRegs);
6068 m_jit.loadDouble(CCallHelpers::Address(baseGPR, DateInstance::offsetOfInternalNumber()), temp1FPR);
6069 auto isNaN = m_jit.branchIfNaN(temp1FPR);
6070
6071 static const double msPerSecondConstant = msPerSecond;
6072 m_jit.loadDouble(TrustedImmPtr(&msPerSecondConstant), temp2FPR);
6073 m_jit.divDouble(temp1FPR, temp2FPR, temp3FPR);
6074 m_jit.floorDouble(temp3FPR, temp3FPR);
6075 m_jit.mulDouble(temp3FPR, temp2FPR, temp3FPR);
6076 m_jit.subDouble(temp1FPR, temp3FPR, temp1FPR);
6077 m_jit.truncateDoubleToInt32(temp1FPR, resultRegs.payloadGPR());
6078 m_jit.boxInt32(resultRegs.payloadGPR(), resultRegs);
6079
6080 isNaN.link(&m_jit);
6081 jsValueResult(resultRegs, node);
6082 break;
6083 }
6084
6085 case DatePrototypeGetFullYearIntrinsic:
6086 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfYear(), operationDateGetFullYear);
6087 break;
6088 case DatePrototypeGetUTCFullYearIntrinsic:
6089 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfYear(), operationDateGetUTCFullYear);
6090 break;
6091 case DatePrototypeGetMonthIntrinsic:
6092 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfMonth(), operationDateGetMonth);
6093 break;
6094 case DatePrototypeGetUTCMonthIntrinsic:
6095 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfMonth(), operationDateGetUTCMonth);
6096 break;
6097 case DatePrototypeGetDateIntrinsic:
6098 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfMonthDay(), operationDateGetDate);
6099 break;
6100 case DatePrototypeGetUTCDateIntrinsic:
6101 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfMonthDay(), operationDateGetUTCDate);
6102 break;
6103 case DatePrototypeGetDayIntrinsic:
6104 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfWeekDay(), operationDateGetDay);
6105 break;
6106 case DatePrototypeGetUTCDayIntrinsic:
6107 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfWeekDay(), operationDateGetUTCDay);
6108 break;
6109 case DatePrototypeGetHoursIntrinsic:
6110 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfHour(), operationDateGetHours);
6111 break;
6112 case DatePrototypeGetUTCHoursIntrinsic:
6113 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfHour(), operationDateGetUTCHours);
6114 break;
6115 case DatePrototypeGetMinutesIntrinsic:
6116 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfMinute(), operationDateGetMinutes);
6117 break;
6118 case DatePrototypeGetUTCMinutesIntrinsic:
6119 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfMinute(), operationDateGetUTCMinutes);
6120 break;
6121 case DatePrototypeGetSecondsIntrinsic:
6122 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfSecond(), operationDateGetSeconds);
6123 break;
6124 case DatePrototypeGetUTCSecondsIntrinsic:
6125 emitGetCode(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeUTCCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTimeUTC() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfSecond(), operationDateGetUTCSeconds);
6126 break;
6127
6128 case DatePrototypeGetTimezoneOffsetIntrinsic: {
6129 emitGetCodeWithCallback(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfUTCOffsetInMinute(), operationDateGetTimezoneOffset, [&] (GPRReg offsetGPR) {
6130 m_jit.neg32(offsetGPR);
6131 });
6132 break;
6133 }
6134
6135 case DatePrototypeGetYearIntrinsic: {
6136 emitGetCodeWithCallback(DateInstanceData::offsetOfGregorianDateTimeCachedForMS(), DateInstanceData::offsetOfCachedGregorianDateTime() + GregorianDateTime::offsetOfYear(), operationDateGetYear, [&] (GPRReg yearGPR) {
6137 m_jit.sub32(TrustedImm32(1900), yearGPR);
6138 });
6139 break;
6140 }
6141
6142 default:
6143 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
6144 }
6145}
